I have been on the hunt for the perfect standing desk ever since; however, nothing has matched both my pickiness and my budget.
That is, until the day that I was scrambling to pull my dog from my bookcase yet again (her favorite pastime is trying to scale it like it’s Mount Everest), and I realized that I’d had the perfect standing desk all along.
What follows are the steps for making a standing desk from a bookcase, based on my own experience.
Step 1: Choose the right bookcaseThe point of a standing desk is to get you out of your chair and to relieve strain on your neck and back.
Having a standing desk won’t be of much help if you strain your back.